TITLE: Managing Components on an EliCS Entity
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to add, access, and modify components of an entity in EliCS. It assumes the existence of a custom component (`YourComponent`) and demonstrates adding it with initial data, accessing a value using a key, and modifying a value using `setValue`. Requires that 'your-components' is a valid module in the project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elixr-games/elics/blob/main/docs/architecture/entity.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { YourComponent } from 'your-components';

// Adding a component
entity.addComponent(YourComponent, {
	/* initial data */
});

// Accessing a component's value
const value = entity.getValue(YourComponent, 'key');

// Modifying a component's value
entity.setValue(YourComponent, 'key', newValue);
```

