TITLE: Registering EliCS System with Priority and Config
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates registering a system (`EnemySystem`) with the `World`, specifying both configuration data (`configData`) and an execution priority. The `priority` value influences the order in which systems are updated each frame.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elixr-games/elics/blob/main/docs/architecture/system.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
const world = new World();
world.registerComponent(EnemyComponent).registerSystem(EnemySystem, {
	configData: { healthRegen: 0.5 },
	priority: 10,
});
```

